Here's a comprehensive list of Docker CLI commands, organized by category.
Container Lifecycle

docker run — create and start a container
docker create — create a container without starting
docker start — start a stopped container
docker stop — gracefully stop a container
docker restart — restart a container
docker pause — pause processes in a container
docker unpause — resume paused container
docker kill — force-stop (send SIGKILL)
docker rm — remove a container
docker rename — rename a container
docker wait — block until container stops (print exit code)

Container Interaction / Inspection

docker exec — run a command in a running container
docker attach — attach to a running container
docker logs — fetch container logs (-f follow)
docker top — running processes in a container
docker stats — live resource usage stats
docker inspect — low-level details (JSON)
docker diff — changes to container filesystem
docker port — port mappings
docker cp — copy files between container and host
docker export — export container filesystem as tar
docker update — update container resource limits

Images

docker build — build an image from a Dockerfile
docker pull — download an image from a registry
docker push — upload an image to a registry
docker images — list images
docker rmi — remove an image
docker tag — tag an image
docker history — show image layers/history
docker save — save image(s) to a tar archive
docker load — load image(s) from a tar archive
docker import — create image from a tarball
docker commit — create image from a container's changes
docker inspect — image details (also works on images)

Registry / Auth

docker login — authenticate to a registry
docker logout — log out of a registry
docker search — search Docker Hub for images

Networking

docker network create — create a network
docker network ls — list networks
docker network rm — remove a network
docker network connect — connect container to network
docker network disconnect — disconnect container
docker network inspect — network details
docker network prune — remove unused networks

Volumes

docker volume create — create a volume
docker volume ls — list volumes
docker volume rm — remove a volume
docker volume inspect — volume details
docker volume prune — remove unused volumes

System / Cleanup

docker system df — disk usage
docker system prune — remove unused data (containers, networks, images, cache)
docker system info — system-wide info
docker system events — real-time events stream
docker info — display system info
docker version — Docker version info
docker ps — list running containers (-a for all)
docker container prune — remove stopped containers
docker image prune — remove unused images

Management Command Groups (modern syntax)

Docker organizes commands into management groups; many of the above have equivalents:

docker container (run, ls, rm, start, stop, exec, logs, inspect, prune…)
docker image (build, ls, rm, pull, push, tag, history, prune…)
docker network (create, ls, rm, connect, inspect, prune…)
docker volume (create, ls, rm, inspect, prune…)
docker system (df, prune, info, events…)
docker context (create, ls, use, rm — manage daemon endpoints)
docker builder (build, prune — manage builds)
docker manifest (create, push, inspect — multi-arch manifests)
docker plugin (install, ls, rm, enable, disable)
docker trust (sign, inspect — content trust)

BuildKit / Buildx

docker buildx build — extended build (multi-arch, cache)
docker buildx create — create a builder instance
docker buildx ls — list builders
docker buildx use — switch builder
docker buildx rm — remove builder
docker buildx prune — clean build cache
docker buildx bake — build from a file (HCL/JSON/Compose)

Docker Compose (v2 plugin)

docker compose up — create and start services (-d detached)
docker compose down — stop and remove services
docker compose build — build service images
docker compose start/stop/restart — control services
docker compose ps — list containers
docker compose logs — view service logs
docker compose exec — exec into a service
docker compose run — run a one-off command
docker compose pull/push — pull/push service images
docker compose config — validate/view merged config
docker compose scale — scale a service (or up --scale)
docker compose pause/unpause
docker compose top
docker compose cp

Docker Swarm

docker swarm init — initialize a swarm
docker swarm join — join a swarm
docker swarm leave — leave a swarm
docker swarm join-token — manage join tokens
docker swarm update — update swarm config
docker node ls/inspect/rm/update/promote/demote — manage nodes
docker service create/ls/ps/rm/scale/update/logs/inspect/rollback — manage services
docker stack deploy/ls/ps/rm/services — manage stacks
docker secret create/ls/rm/inspect — manage secrets
docker config create/ls/rm/inspect — manage configs

Other / Misc

docker scout — image vulnerability/analysis (CVEs, recommendations)
docker init — scaffold Dockerfile/Compose/dockerignore
docker checkpoint — checkpoint/restore (experimental)
docker debug — debug containers (Docker Desktop)

That covers container lifecycle, images, networking, volumes, system management, the modern management-group syntax, Buildx, Compose v2, and Swarm. Daily essentials are run, ps, exec, logs, build, images, pull/push, plus compose up/down.